recalc-dims=\"1\" /></p>\n<p>TwitterCounter plugin allows you to integrate <a href=\"http://twittercounter.com\" rel=\"nofollow\">TwitterCounter.com</a> buttons on your blog.</p>\n<p>Additionally, you can add the Twitter Widget to your blog, which shows which twitter users recently visited your blog or website. Manually add where you would like to display the badge / remote or use the WordPress sidebar widgets instead.</p>\n<p>This release fixes a <a href=\"http://techtites.com/2013/how-to-prevent-csrf-vulnerability-in-wordpress-plugins-and-themes/\">potential CSRF vulnerability</a> and also includes fixes for PHP in strict mode.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re already using TwitterCounter on your blog, then you can upgrade the plugin from within your WordPress interface itself. New users can get hold of the plugin <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/twittercounter/\">here</a>.</p>\n</div><hr style=\"border-top:black solid 1px\" /><a href=\"http://ajaydsouza.com/archives/2013/07/21/twittercounter-v1-6-1/\">TwitterCounter v1.6.1</a> was first posted on July 21, 2013 at 10:35 pm.<br />© 2003-2013 \"<a href=\"http://ajaydsouza.com\">Ajay - On the Road called Life</a>\". All rights reserved.<br />\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://ajaydsouza.com/archives/2013/07/21/twittercounter-v1-6-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\"